Conclusion: Revolutions best satisfies the explicit single‑artist, career‑spanning, melodic and vintage‑character criteria in my self‑introduction, while the other CD’s patchwork remixes, loudness/tonal shifts and less clearly retro/uptempo profile make it a poorer fit.

